gomodel:SYNGO_5380  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: Reduced spine density and increased spine size in CAP1-KO neurons.\n\nFigure 3: CAP1 controls actin turnover and F-actin distribution in spines.\n\"Hence, our data revealed an altered F-actin distribution within CAP1-KO spines, suggesting a role for CAP1 in organizing the postsynaptic actin cytoskeleton. Interestingly, F-actin disorganization was associated with an altered distribution of key PSD proteins. Together, we identified CAP1 as a novel regulator of the postsynaptic actin cytoskeleton relevant for both actin dynamics and F-actin organization.\"\n\nFigure 4: Helical folded domain and CARP domain are relevant for CAP1 function in spines.\n\nFigure 7: CAP1 and cofilin1 are functionally interdependent in spines.. Experimental description: \"Generation of CAP1flx/flx and Cfl1flx/flx mice has been described before\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5380" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

